19/02/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian President Boris Tadic was re-elected leader of the opposition Democratic Party (DS) at the party congress Saturday (18 February) in Belgrade.
Afterwards, Tadic presented his ideas for establishing a civil forum within DS, and urged party members to sharpen their political skills.
He also said the DS would place a priority on fighting corruption in local administration.
(Politika - 19/02/06)
